        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 7 at 11:13PM MDT until August 7 at 11:45PM MDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 1112 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 7 miles southeast of New England to 5 miles southwest
of Reeder, moving east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Mott, Scranton, Reeder, Regent, Bucyrus, Gascoyne, and Buffalo
Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
